  "notes": "Data cross-verified across three independent sources that agree exactly: (1) RFEG club page (recorrido LV25-3, valid from 03/09/2022) with per-hole par/hcp/meters and Vc/Vs per tee and gender; (2) the club's official printed scorecard (tarjeta) PDF, which matches every per-hole distance, par and hcp; (3) the club's official RFEG WHS equivalence-table PDFs (men and women), which confirm all CR/slope values. Golfshake's yardage totals (6706/6284/5767/5217 yd) convert to the same meter totals, though its SSS/slope values are outdated pre-2022 ratings. Internal consistency verified: pars sum 36+36=72, stroke indexes 1-18 each used once, each tee's 18 distances sum exactly to the published total. All tee distances are measured to the center of the green. The stroke-index allocation is the same on all tees and both genders per RFEG. RFEG also lists a separate 'Naranjas' (orange) rated recorrido: par 58 over 18 holes (a 9-hole short loop of 1337 m, par 29, played twice - this is the La Cala par-3/short course), rated CR 55.4/Slope 73 (men) and 57.4/83 (women); it is excluded from the tees array because its hole pars (3,3,4,3,4,3,3,3,3) differ from the main 18-hole card and the schema supports only one hole layout. Amarillas (yellow) tees are mapped to color 'gold' per the allowed color list."
